template<class X >
X nextlimit::rf_sdk::RFBaseObj< T >::getParameter ( const std::string &  name)

getParameter:

Gets the value of THIS Node 's Parameter given by its name( name ). As this is a templatized method you would need to indicate the type of the parameter. Example: int valueParameter = thisNode.getParameter<int>( "nameParameter" );

Parameters:
[in]name/ Node 's parameter name
Returns:
: Node 's parameter value

template<class T>
sdk_type::SdkParamType nextlimit::rf_sdk::RFBaseObj< T >::getParameterType ( const std::string &  paramName)

getParameterType:

Gets THIS Node 's Parameter type given by its name( paramName ).

Parameters:
[in]paramName/ Node 's parameter name
Returns:
: Node 's parameter type, values in Param_Type [ TYPE_FLOAT TYPE_DOUBLE TYPE_LIST TYPE_INT TYPE_BOOL TYPE_EDIT TYPE_CBUTTON TYPE_BUTTON TYPE_BROWSE TYPE_VECTOR TYPE_COLOR ]
  • If the node has not a parameter with name ( paramName ) then it returns -1;

template<class T>
void nextlimit::rf_sdk::RFBaseObj< T >::setParameter ( const std::string &  name,
const Color &  value 
)

setParameter:

Sets THIS Node 's Parameter value given by its name( name ). The parameter name is the one that can be seen in the user interface. It is not case sensitive. The value can be any type that is accepted for the parameters in the user interface. Care must be taken when using this function about the type of the values and the parameter names, a hard type and name check is done reporting the corresponding errors to the user in any case.

Parameters:
[in]name/ Node 's parameter name
[in]value/ Node 's parameter new value
